Progress.title: The Progress Schema
examples: A mixture of market-rate and affordable housing on a 13.6-acre tract.

Demolition of 180 existing public housing units. Construction of new housing units to include 50 senior units, and 40 market rate units.  Plans also include 7,000sqft of community space and associated site work.  For senior living units, one-bedroom will be 560sqft and two-bedrooms will be 830sqft. For the multifamily units, one-bedroom will be 625sqft, two-bedrooms will be 1,050sqft, three-bedrooms will be 1,100sqft, and four-bedrooms will be 1,900sqft.  This project is set to be built in phases.  Phase 1A will be 129 units of 1, 2, 3, and 4-bedroom multifamily apartments. Phase 1B will be 50 units of 1 and 2-bedroom senior apartments. Phase 2A will be 101 units of 1, 2, 3, and 4-bedroom multifamily apartments. Phase 2B will be 40 units of market rate 1, 2, and 3-bedroom units.  As of November 2014, this project is seeking entitlement approvals from the city.  Once these approvals are granted, the architect will move to plan the approval.
